Title: What is the Honor Code?
Descript: From the very beginning of Hillsdale, our commitment has been to develop the minds and improve the hearts of our students.We believe that the ultimate aim of education is to produce true liberty of the mind AND the soul. This aim requires us to pursue moral virtue with the same rigor as intellectual virtue.This is why every student at Hillsdale commits themselves to the Honor Code. This code isn<U+0092>t a list of rules, or do<U+0092>s and don<U+0092>ts.It's a calling to a greater way to live.A Hillsdale College student is honorable in conduct, honest in word and deed, dutiful in study and service, and respectful of the rights of others.Through education the student rises to self-government.This code is a commitment of one<U+0092>s heart and mind to the highest moral character - to those things that are the most good, true, and beautiful. Title: One Gram:High leverage Leadership tools | Kaustubh Panse | TEDxNMIMSShirpur
Descript: One can't learn everything in life so the secret is to learn tools which give great leverage. One gram leadership is just that. Kaustubh Panse is a Mechanical Engineer, Entrepreneur and a Business coach. With 10+ years of experience in the field of Training & consulting, He believes that success in life doesn't only depend upon technical skills but we also need EQ i.e. Emotional quotient in the Personality. He has been handling the team of 100+ people from last 10years. This talk was given at a TEDx event using the TED conference format but independently organized by a local community. Learn more at https://www.ted.com/tedx
